Parliament, Thursday, 22 November 2018 – A joint meeting of the Standing and Select Committees on Appropriations will tomorrow (Friday, 23 November 2018) hold joint public hearings on the 2018 Medium-term Budget Policy Statement; 2018 Adjustments Appropriation Bill [B35-2018]; and 2018 Special Appropriation Bill [B36-2018]. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date:         Friday, 23 November 2018
	Time:         09:00 – 12:00
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building The Standing Committee on Appropriations will thereafter have a hearing with Department of Basic Education on the 2018 Adjustments Appropriation Bill. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date:         Friday, 23 November 2018
	Time:         12:00 – 14:00
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING AND SELECT COMMITTEES ON APPROPRIATIONS, MS YVONNE PHOSA AND MR CHAREL DE BEER. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
